# Mergiraf semantic merge driver — auto-resolves conflicts using tree-sitter
# AST diffs (33 languages, mergiraf.org). Slice 5 of `daemon-parallel-worktree-launch`,
# also addresses operator directive 2026-05-06 ("ensure that minsky itself will be
# able to resolve git conflicts when it merges its work").
#
# Activation:
#   node scripts/setup-mergiraf.mjs   # idempotent — installs binary if missing,
#                                       sets `git config merge.mergiraf.{name,driver,recursive}`
#
# Without the binary, git falls back to the default merge driver silently — no
# regression. With the binary, daemon-vs-daemon and operator-vs-daemon merges
# on the file types below auto-resolve when the conflict is structural
# (e.g. TASKS.md task-block insertions on both sides) rather than semantic.

*.ts merge=mergiraf
*.tsx merge=mergiraf
*.mjs merge=mergiraf
*.js merge=mergiraf
*.jsx merge=mergiraf
*.json merge=mergiraf
*.md merge=mergiraf
*.yml merge=mergiraf
*.yaml merge=mergiraf
